[h3 id=JellyBeanWalkthrough
 
	" Jelly Bean Walkthrough
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Due to the positive initial feedback, here is a more detailed explanation of the jelly beans used in the run. If somebody has clear understanding of the possible puns in the names and functions of the jelly beans, please share the joy.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"In the beginning of the run I use...
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Tangerine=Trampoline
 
	" Tangerine = Trampoline
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To get the bag of jelly beans including lime.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Lime=Key
 
	" Lime = Key
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"This opens the door. Then I run right to get another bag of jelly beans. Then I use punch.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Punch=Hole
 
	" Punch = Hole
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To get down fast. Here we have some very heavy lag for an unknown reason.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Ketchup=Teleportstheblobtothespotwherethebeanlands
 
	" Ketchup = Teleports the blob to the spot where the bean lands
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"I use this to position the blob, so that he catches up and is not left too much behind.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Strawberry=Bridge
 
	" Strawberry = Bridge
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"I throw the strawberry bean off-screen straight to the blob's mouth, so that he starts forming a bridge. Then I whistle to cancel the bridge at the correct location to make the boy fall through the ground. Too bad there's leathal falling damage, which causes some clumsiness throughout the run.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Ketchupagain
 
	" Ketchup again
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To put the blob in a good trampoline position.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Tangerineagain
 
	" Tangerine again
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To go up the tower. The large boiling pot is lethal and it could be frozen with mint jelly bean, but it is not necessary, because the blob can be positioned on the edge of the pot, which is just enough to not hit the ceiling when bouncing upwards the tower.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Ketchupagain
 
	" Ketchup again
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"To summon the blob here.
	$LF
]p
[h4 id=Honey=Hummingbird
 
	" Honey = Hummingbird
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"By transforming into a bird, the blob can open Blobette's prison cage. The princess would then fall down and land on the frozen pot and walk to safety. It is a shame that the speed-oriented movie can't show how the princess Blobette now falls 
	[em 
		"into
	]em
	" the boiling pot, because the water was not frozen.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The rest of the movie consists of using ketchup and punch to travel fast to the throne room for some blob romance.
	$LF
